%N A394913 a(n) is the number of sides of the highest-sided polygonal face in Johnson solid J_n.
%H A394913 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Johnson_solids">List of Johnson solids</a>.
%e A394913 Johnson solid J_32 (pentagonal orthocupolarotunda) has triangular, square and pentagonal faces, so a(32) = 5.
%t A394913 A394913[n_] := Max[Map[Length, PolyhedronData["J" <> ToString[n], "FaceIndices"]]];
%t A394913 Array[A394913, 92] (* Gives the full sequence *)
%o A394913 (Python)
%o A394913 import requests
%o A394913 JS=requests.get("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/levskaya/polyhedronisme/master/johnson_solids.js")
%o A394913 JS=[locs for block in JS.text.split("polyhedron();")[1:-1] if not exec(
%o A394913    "if 1:\n"+block.split("return")[0].replace("poly.",''), {}, locs:={})]
%o A394913 A394913 = lambda n: max(len(f)for f in JS[n-1]['faces']) # _M. F. Hasler_, Apr 10 2026
